trapTable.name: trapTable
trapTable.description: This table houses information for transmitting traps. This table is not associated with trivial authentication.

trapEntry.name: trapEntry
trapEntry.description: Each entry contains a community name for the SNMP trap PDU, network addresses of who receives traps from this device and a trap status of Enable or Disable.

trapIndex.name: trapIndex
trapIndex.description: A unique value for each trap entry that indexes the table.

trapCommunityName.name: trapCommunityName
trapCommunityName.description: The community name that will be used within the SNMP trap PDU.

trapStatus.name: trapStatus
trapStatus.description: This object is checked to determine if traps should be sent to the corresponding network address associated with it.

trapIPAddr.name: trapIPAddr
trapIPAddr.description: The network address of the device that will receive traps from this agent.

trapSrcParty.name: trapSrcParty
trapSrcParty.description: This object administratively defines operations of the source SNMP protocol entity. When processing a SNMP message, the entity acts as a SNMP party.

trapDstParty.name: trapDstParty
trapDstParty.description: This object administratively defines operations of the destination SNMP protocol entity. When processing a SNMP message, the entity acts as a SNMP party.
